<title>USA: Southwest Securities acquires firm's unit.</title>
<headline>Southwest Securities acquires firm's unit.</headline>
<dateline>DALLAS 1997-06-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Southwest Securities Group Inc said it has signed a letter of intent to purchase the customer assets of the Dallas brokerage firm of Cullum &amp; Sandow Securities Inc.</p>
<p>Terms were not disclosed.</p>
<p>It said it plans to merge the firm into Brokers Transaction Services, a Southwest subsidiary.</p>
<p>Both BTS and Cullum &amp; Sandow provide home office and administrative support to independent registered representatives who conduct their securities business through the broker/dealers under exclusive agreements.</p>
<p>The transaction is expected to close within the next 45 days.</p>
<p>((-- New York Newsdesk 212-859-1610))</p>
